{"article_id":"GNd1LeOAPv8MIpUL","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Obama was heading to Detroit Monday afternoon","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to continue campaigning for tax hikes on top earners","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"-- a day after a face-to-face meeting with House Speaker John Boehner","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"that offered slight hope","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"the two could be making progress toward a deal .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"The president and the speaker met Sunday afternoon at the White House for the first time in weeks .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"It came","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"after Boehner publicly chided Obama on Friday for the lack of progress to date ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"accusing the president of having `` wasted another week . ''","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"Both sides were tightlipped about the surprise Sunday afternoon meeting .","depth":3},{"id":10,"text":"But","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"instead of emerging from the talks","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"complaining about each other ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"as was the case","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"following phone calls last week ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"each side released an identical statement .","depth":5},{"id":16,"text":"`` This afternoon , the President and Speaker Boehner met at the White House","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"to discuss efforts","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"to resolve the fiscal cliff .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"We 're not reading out details of the conversation ,","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"but the lines of communication remain open , ''","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"the statement","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"released by each office","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"said .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Lawmakers and the White House have three weeks to reach a deal ,","depth":3},{"id":25,"text":"before a potentially crippling set of tax hikes and spending cuts takes effect .","depth":3},{"id":26,"text":"Boehner last week put a counter-proposal on the table","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"that included $ 800 billion in revenue increases over the next decade .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"While Boehner cast that as a significant concession ,","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"Obama said","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"it did n't go far enough","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"because it did n't include an increase in tax rates for the top 2 percent .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"Boehner , though , is facing some pressure from Republicans","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"to give a little bit more .","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"The speaker is effectively caught between two competing wings of the Republican Party .","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"Some say","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Congress should not raise any taxes ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"and were disappointed","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"he went so far as to put any revenue on the table .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"However , a growing number of Republicans are suggesting","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"the party should give Obama what he wants on tax rates","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"-- and focus instead on winning entitlement cuts","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"once that is cleared away .","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"Sen. Bob Corker , R-Tenn. , became the latest Republican","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"to open the door to tax rate hikes during an interview on `` Fox News Sunday .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"'' `` There is a growing group of folks","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"that are looking at this","depth":14},{"id":47,"text":"and realizing","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"that we do n't have a lot of cards","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"as it relates to the tax issue , before year-end .","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"I mean ,","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"we have one house ,","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"that 's it , ''","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"Corker said .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"Corker suggested","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"that Republicans instead focus on extracting entitlement cuts as part of the debt-ceiling negotiations .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"`` Republicans know","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"that they have the debt ceiling","depth":15},{"id":58,"text":"that 's coming up right around the corner ,","depth":15},{"id":59,"text":"and the leverage is going to shift ,","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"as soon as we get beyond this issue , ''","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"Corker said on `` Fox News Sunday .","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"'' `` The leverage is going to shift to our side ,","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"where hopefully we 'll do the same thing","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"we did last time . ''","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"Corker said","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"if the president wants to raise the debt limit by $ 2 trillion ,","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"Republicans should press for $ 2 trillion in spending cuts .","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"That prospect is sure to infuriate the White House .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"After the bruising debt-ceiling fight from 2011 , Obama recently warned","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"that he will not `` play that game '' again .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"`` We 've got to break that habit","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"before it starts , ''","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"the president said .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"The president argues","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"that fights over the debt ceiling merely shake global confidence in the country 's ability","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"to pay its bills ,","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"and as part of talks over the looming fiscal crisis has called for a de facto permanent increase in the debt limit .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"It 's unclear whether Obama might drop that demand","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"if he gets what he wants on tax rates .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"His campaign-style visit to Detroit , though , threatens to muddy the waters on talks .","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"Rep. Kevin McCarthy , R-Calif. , the No . 3 Republican in the House , suggested Sunday","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"that the president 's itinerary has left Republicans","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"to negotiate with themselves .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"`` He 's been to Pennsylvania .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Tomorrow he is going to Detroit .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"It 's now time","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"to govern .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"The election is over , ''","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"he said on NBC 's `` Meet the Press . ''","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"Democratic Illinois Sen. Dick Durbin countered","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"that Obama `` is a phone call away","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"and you know it . ''","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":187,"left":117,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":102,"right":116,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":98,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":95,"right":97,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":2,"right":96,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":5,"right":100,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":6,"right":99,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":9,"right":115,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":115,"left":107,"right":114,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":106,"right":15,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":106,"left":10,"right":105,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":105,"left":103,"right":104,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":11,"right":12